\begin_layout Section
Combinations 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Combining results from multiple studies that analyse similar conditions
 provides an insight into the patterns shared among the experiments.
 However the heterogeneous nature of the data makes it difficult to compare
 different datasets.
 Therefore, the individual experiments are often not directly compatible
 for producing a single combined data set on which to conduct a second meta-anal
ysis.
 Fortunately, one can still produce a combined test of significance of alteratio
n events across a set of experiments with similar conditions.
 
\end_layout

